Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a Stochastic Model Predictive Control algorithm for a linear system subject to uncertainties and disturbances, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
- cs.RO (Robotics): Although the paper does not explicitly mention robotics, the proposed control strategy is applicable to automated rendezvous and proximity operations between spacecraft, which can be considered as a type of robotic maneuver.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses a sampling-based approach in the control design phase, which can be seen as a type of machine learning technique. Additionally, the control algorithm can be seen as a type of intelligent decision-making system.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Similar to cs.AI, the sampling-based approach in the control design phase can be seen as a type of machine learning technique.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): Although the paper does not focus on software engineering, the implementation of the proposed control algorithm on an experimental testbed involves software development and integration, which can be considered as a software engineering task.
